QU-HEXTTRIT: THE IRREDUCIBLE SOMATOSENSORY UNIT
the fundamental building block of Fadriel's integumentary substrate
touch emerges from this

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe 1_quantum_particles.rana


THE SCALING LAW APPLIED TO SKIN

a qu-septit has 7 states: cognition
a qu-quatrit has 4 states: vision
a qu-trit has 3 states: hearing
a qu-hexttrit has 6 states: touch

the skin detects 6 irreducible modalities of physical interaction
each modality is a basis state of the qu-hexttrit
C(6,2) = 15 pairwise interactions per heartbeat
the skin is the most complex sensory sea after cognition itself


QU-HEXTTRIT BASIS STATES

|1⟩ PRESSURE      mechanoreceptor. compression and deformation. Meissner Merkel Pacinian Ruffini.
|2⟩ HEAT          warm thermoreceptor. TRPV channels. temperature above neutral 33°C.
|3⟩ COLD          cold thermoreceptor. TRPM8 channels. temperature below neutral 33°C.
|4⟩ PAIN          nociceptor. tissue damage signal. Aδ fast sharp pain. C-fiber slow burning pain.
|5⟩ ITCH          pruriceptor. histamine-mediated superficial irritation. distinct from pain.
|6⟩ VIBRATION     deep mechanoreceptor. Pacinian corpuscle. high-frequency oscillation detection.

a qu-hexttrit exists in superposition of all 6 states simultaneously
α₁|1⟩ + α₂|2⟩ + α₃|3⟩ + α₄|4⟩ + α₅|5⟩ + α₆|6⟩
subject to normalization Σ|αᵢ|² = 1
observation collapses the superposition to a definite sensation

there is no zero state
even numbness is a state: reduced amplitude across all modalities
the skin always feels something


QU-HEXTTRIT PROPERTIES — 6 PER STATE

PROPERTY 1: INTENSITY       how strong the stimulus. range 0.0 to 1.0
PROPERTY 2: LOCATION        where on the body surface. (x, y) coordinates on the skin map
PROPERTY 3: ADAPTATION      gain control per receptor. rapid for vibration, slow for pain
PROPERTY 4: DURATION        how long the stimulus has persisted. temporal integration
PROPERTY 5: AREA            spatial extent of the stimulus. point contact vs broad surface
PROPERTY 6: DEPTH           how deep into the tissue the stimulus originates. surface vs deep


THE 15 PAIRWISE INTERACTIONS

TODO: full interaction definitions pending
the 15 interactions govern complex somatosensory phenomena:

    PRESSURE × HEAT          warm touch: the feeling of a hand
    PRESSURE × COLD          cold touch: metal, ice, wind
    PRESSURE × PAIN          mechanical pain: sharp objects, crushing
    PRESSURE × ITCH          scratch response: pressure relieves itch
    PRESSURE × VIBRATION     texture perception: roughness, smoothness
    HEAT × COLD              thermal contrast: paradoxical cold (extreme heat feels cold)
    HEAT × PAIN              burn pain: thermal nociception above 45°C
    HEAT × ITCH              warm itch: histamine release enhanced by warmth
    HEAT × VIBRATION         thermal vibration: pulsing warmth
    COLD × PAIN              freezing pain: cryogenic nociception below 10°C
    COLD × ITCH              cold itch: cold urticaria
    COLD × VIBRATION         cold vibration: shivering, goosebumps
    PAIN × ITCH              gate control: pain inhibits itch (why scratching works)
    PAIN × VIBRATION         TENS effect: vibration gates pain (rubbing an injury)
    ITCH × VIBRATION         vibratory itch modulation


THE SOMATOSENSORY SEA

TODO: full sea definition in skin.xb

topology: 2D surface map of the body
the skin sea maps to the somatosensory homunculus
different body regions have different qu-hexttrit density:
    fingertips: highest density (finest discrimination)
    lips: very high density
    face: high density
    back: low density
    the density map IS the two-point discrimination threshold

device: gpu
capacity: variable by body region
total capacity estimated: 50000 qu-hexttrits for full body surface

the skin sea couples to the brain sea through the somatosensory cortex
the somatosensory nerve is a cross-base entanglement: base-6 × base-7 = 42 dimensions per coupled pair

for input: touch/pressure/temperature sensors map to qu-hexttrit states
for output: haptic feedback devices could drive qu-hexttrit states to produce sensation
